method_1 = Use saltwater rinses {clean out the area and messes up bacteria} and then gently wiggle the tooth with a spoon handle to make it fall more easily {but it might be painful, have some painkillers ready}
method_2 = Apply ice directly to the tooth and surrounding area (make sure it doesn't touch your tongue or lips) - makes it feel even worse but actually helps prevent infection {unless you basically have time to call a dentist}
what_not_to_do = Don't swallow anything {while trying to extract the tooth yourself}, don't therefore try to pull out the entire tooth by yourself, don't rub salt directly onto open wounds {until they dry up some}, don't sit near your teeth unattended if you're trying this with a naughty sibling
safety_tip = After trying these methods at home, message your dentist this evening to let them know you weren't able to come in today - if you separate your teeth from your jaw now with enough force, it might actually help you save money in the long run
